# Cursor Agent Team Operating Contract

This project uses the shared agent-team template in the repository root.

Before making changes:

- Read `@AGENTS.md` for the shared operating contract.
- Use `@prompts/lead-agent.md` when acting as the lead agent.
- Use `@prompts/worker-agent.md` when acting as a bounded worker.
- Choose the relevant workflow from `@workflows/` before decomposing work.
- Read the relevant module folder under `@docs/modules/` when the task targets a module.
- Use `@templates/task-brief.md` for lead task briefs.
- Use `@templates/handoff-note.md` for worker handoffs.

Cursor-specific expectations:

- Treat this rule as the project-level adapter for Cursor Agent.
- Keep the reusable docs in this repo as the source of truth.
- Do not copy large sections of the template into new Cursor rules unless the shared contract changes.
- Prefer small, reviewable edits and report verification evidence before claiming completion.
- If a task is small or tightly coupled, keep it in one Cursor Agent session instead of forcing parallel work.

When delegating or simulating worker roles, keep ownership scopes disjoint and include the required handoff sections from `@templates/handoff-note.md`.
